<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="P" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Poverty" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Poverty,</orth> want of riches, indigence: <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.1.150" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. II, 1, 150</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 1.2.85" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. I, 2, 85</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.269" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 269</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.269" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 269</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mv 4.1.271" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. IV, 1, 271</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.5.100" default="NO" valid="yes">As III, 5, 100</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 5.2.7" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 4.4.647" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 4, 647</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 4.2.76" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A IV, 2, 76</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.2.146" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 2, 146</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.3.75" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 3, 75</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.1.116" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 116</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.3.84" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 3, 84</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.7.159" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 7, 159</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 4.2.149" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 IV, 2, 149</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 5.1.75" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. V, 1, 75</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 5.1.75" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. V, 1, 75</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tim 4.2.14" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 2, 14</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 4.2.50" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. IV, 2, 50</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 1.4.30" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. I, 4, 30</bibl>. Abstr. pro concr., == 1) one poor, or poor persons: <cit><quote>to think my p. is treacherous,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 1.3.67" default="NO" valid="yes">As I, 3, 67</bibl></cit> (== poor I). <cit><quote>you houseless p.</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 3.4.26" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 4, 26</bibl></cit>. 2) a little paltry stock of goods: <cit><quote>although thou steal thee all my p.</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 40.10" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 40, 10</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>what p. my Muse brings forth,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 3.103.1" default="NO" valid="yes">103, 1</bibl></cit>.
